01:05.000 --> 01:07.931
Man: IT'S ALL ABOUT THE HEART,
HOW MUCH HEART YOU HAVE LEFT.

01:07.931 --> 01:09.896
♪ I'VE GOT EVERY REASON
TO FIGHT ♪

01:09.896 --> 01:11.103
WATCH OUT!

01:11.103 --> 01:12.896
♪ GLADIATOR ♪[ GROANS ]

01:12.896 --> 01:14.103
♪ GLADIATOR ♪

01:14.103 --> 01:15.586
BIG WAVE! BIG ONE!

01:15.586 --> 01:17.551
HOLD ON!

01:17.551 --> 01:20.448
♪ BONE SHAKER, DOMINATOR ♪WHOO!

01:20.448 --> 01:22.896
♪ FREIGHT TRAIN, WRECKING BALL ♪HANG ON, GUYS. HANG ON. HANG ON.

01:22.896 --> 01:24.137
♪ I'M THE GLADIATOR ♪

01:24.137 --> 01:27.724
AAH! AAH!

01:27.724 --> 01:30.241
-WHOO!
-HOLD ON!

01:30.241 --> 01:32.724
MAN UP, FINISH WHAT YOU START.

01:32.724 --> 01:33.896
♪ GLADIATOR ♪

01:33.896 --> 01:39.482
♪♪

01:39.482 --> 01:42.068
[ WIND WHISTLING ]

01:42.068 --> 01:46.206
♪♪

01:46.206 --> 01:49.793
Narrator: WHITE-KNUCKLE HOURS
HAVE TURNED TO DAYS OF TORMENT

01:49.793 --> 01:54.068
UNDER THE REIGN
OF A FRIGID TYRANT -- ELSA.

01:54.068 --> 01:57.000
THE SEASON'S LARGEST STORM
SHOWS NO SIGNS

01:57.000 --> 02:00.103
OF SLOWING DOWN OR MOVING ON.

02:00.103 --> 02:03.034
Casey: IT'S GONNA BE
A COLD FEW DAYS, BOYS.

02:03.034 --> 02:05.896
OLD ELSA DOES NOT WANT
TO PLAY NICE.

02:05.896 --> 02:09.655
Narrator: THREE TITANS --
THE CORNELIA MARIE,

02:09.655 --> 02:13.206
THE SOUTHERN WIND,
AND THE WIZARD --

02:13.206 --> 02:16.275
FIGHT BACK IN THE CRAB-RICH
NORTHERN WATERS

02:16.275 --> 02:18.172
OF THE RUSSIAN LINE.

02:18.172 --> 02:21.034
WE'RE DRIVING STRAIGHT INTO
THE TEETH OF THIS FREEZING SPRAY

02:21.034 --> 02:24.379
AND STORM ELSA.

02:24.379 --> 02:26.965
I'M BASICALLY JUST TRYING
TO SURVIVE.

02:26.965 --> 02:29.758
Narrator: BUT THE LONGER
THAT ELSA'S ASSAULT CONTINUES,

02:29.758 --> 02:32.517
THE LARGER AND MORE POWERFUL
THE SWELLS BECOME.

02:32.517 --> 02:33.862
Keith: WEATHER'S COMING AT ME

02:33.862 --> 02:35.172
EVERY DIFFERENT DIRECTION
RIGHT NOW,

02:35.172 --> 02:37.655
AND I'VE GOT TO PROTECT
MY BOAT AND THE CREW.

02:37.655 --> 02:40.275
Narrator: AND FOR THE CAPTAINS
THAT CHOSE TO FIGHT IT OUT,

02:40.275 --> 02:44.827
THE NIGHTMARE OF
DECK-CLEARING, 4-STORY WAVES

02:44.827 --> 02:46.931
BECOMES A REALITY.

02:46.931 --> 02:49.758
Harley:
THEM WAVES ARE JUST...

02:49.758 --> 02:52.034
THROW YOU AROUND
LIKE A LITTLE RAG DOLL.

02:52.034 --> 02:55.034
AND I FELT IT.
ONCE IT GETS AHOLD OF YOU,

02:55.034 --> 02:56.206
THE ONLY THING
YOU'RE PRAYING FOR

02:56.206 --> 02:58.000
IS THAT YOU'RE GONNA END UP
ON THE BOAT.

02:58.000 --> 03:03.655
♪♪

03:03.655 --> 03:07.137
Narrator: 520 MILES NORTH
OF DUTCH HARBOR,

03:07.137 --> 03:11.137
ON THE STORM-CHURNED SEAS
OF THE RUSSIAN LINE...

03:11.137 --> 03:13.413
IT IS NASTY OUTSIDE.

03:13.413 --> 03:16.965
♪♪

03:16.965 --> 03:20.241
...THE CORNELIA MARIE
POWERS THROUGH 25-FOOT SEAS

03:20.241 --> 03:22.620
TO THE START OF HER NEXT STRING.

03:25.862 --> 03:28.275
Josh: I'M READY TO GO BATTLE
MOTHER NATURE.

03:28.275 --> 03:30.965
IT'S NOT FIT FOR MAN NOR BEAST
OUTSIDE RIGHT NOW.

03:33.965 --> 03:37.482
GOT ABOUT 145,000 ON BOARD
RIGHT NOW.

03:37.482 --> 03:43.172
AFTER THIS STRING, PROBABLY
AROUND 155,000 TO 160,000.

03:43.172 --> 03:44.689
Narrator:
AFTER GAMBLING THEIR SEASON

03:44.689 --> 03:48.000
ON A 520-MILE JOURNEY NORTH,

03:48.000 --> 03:51.586
EVEN THE FORECASTED
60-FOOT MONSTER WAVES

03:51.586 --> 03:55.482
WON'T CHASE CAPTAINS JOSH HARRIS
AND CASEY McMANUS

03:55.482 --> 03:57.827
OFF THE SCORE OF THEIR CAREERS.

03:57.827 --> 03:59.448
Man: OH, THINGS ARE GETTING
CRAZY OUT HERE,

03:59.448 --> 04:02.241
SO EVERYBODY NEEDS
TO BE ON THEIR TOES.

04:08.275 --> 04:15.034
♪♪

04:15.034 --> 04:16.551
Casey: YOU BETTER CATCH
THE REST OF THIS CRAB QUICK

04:16.551 --> 04:18.103
AND GET 'EM IN DOWN.

04:18.103 --> 04:20.034
IT'S WHAT IT IS AT
THIS POINT.

04:22.172 --> 04:24.241
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON!

04:28.310 --> 04:30.689
YEAH, BABY!

04:30.689 --> 04:31.827
OH, YEAH.

04:31.827 --> 04:33.827
WHOO!

04:33.827 --> 04:35.896
Josh: WOW.

04:37.448 --> 04:39.413
WHOO-HOO!

04:42.551 --> 04:44.241
WHOO!

04:47.103 --> 04:48.793
HOLY SCHNIKES!

04:50.620 --> 04:53.034
WHOO!

04:53.034 --> 04:55.482
HOLD ON! [ GROANS ]

04:57.551 --> 04:58.793
[BLEEP]

05:00.931 --> 05:02.793
YEAH!

05:02.793 --> 05:04.482
Josh: OH, MY GOD.

05:04.482 --> 05:07.862
DUDE! [ LAUGHS ]

05:07.862 --> 05:10.034
THAT'S SOME CRAB
RIGHT THERE.

05:14.793 --> 05:16.206
WHOO!

05:17.551 --> 05:19.931
WHOO!

05:24.448 --> 05:25.758
YEAH, THAT'S GONNA HURT.

05:25.758 --> 05:32.000
♪♪

05:35.827 --> 05:41.172
♪♪

05:41.172 --> 05:44.241
Man: WHOA! THAT WASN'T ME!

05:44.241 --> 05:45.689
CENTER TIE!

05:45.689 --> 05:47.344
[ THUD ]WHOA!

05:47.344 --> 05:49.689
WHOA, WHOA! WATCH OUT!
WATCH OUT.

05:49.689 --> 05:52.206
-HOLY [BLEEP],
-JUST WATCH YOURSELF.

05:52.206 --> 05:54.862
-[BLEEP]
-[ SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY ]

05:54.862 --> 05:56.103
AND THE REST GO ON.

05:58.931 --> 06:00.172
WELL...

06:03.448 --> 06:05.551
[BLEEP] THE PICKING HOOK
ACTUALLY SNAP OFF?

06:05.551 --> 06:07.827
IS THAT WHAT HAPPENED?

06:07.827 --> 06:10.379
RIGHT WHEN THE POT WAS COMING
OVER HERE ON THE RAILING,

06:10.379 --> 06:11.586
AND THEN IT JUST WENT "DINK!"

06:11.586 --> 06:15.862
AND SPLASHED RIGHT BACK
IN THE WATER.

06:15.862 --> 06:18.413
Narrator: AS THE FORWARD CRANE
PULLS 2,000 POUNDS

06:18.413 --> 06:22.413
OF STEEL AND CRAB
OUT OF THE WATER,

06:22.413 --> 06:25.448
THE LINE CONNECTED
TO THE PICKING HOOK SNAPS,

06:25.448 --> 06:29.517
SENDING THE POT PLUMMETING BACK
INTO THE BERING SEA,

06:29.517 --> 06:32.413
NEARLY ENSNARING
DECK BOSS D.J. CAMPBELL

06:32.413 --> 06:36.034
AND DRAGGING HIM
TO THE DEPTHS BELOW.

06:36.034 --> 06:37.827
SOMEBODY COULD HAVE
GOT SERIOUSLY INJURED.

06:37.827 --> 06:44.827
♪♪

06:49.275 --> 06:53.758
♪♪

06:53.758 --> 06:55.172
Casey: HAVING A PICKING HOOK
SNAP LIKE THAT

06:55.172 --> 06:57.034
IS PROBABLY ONE OF
THE MOST DANGEROUS THINGS,

06:57.034 --> 07:00.586
'CAUSE IF THE GUY BEHIND YOU
ALREADY HAS HIS LINE ARM

07:00.586 --> 07:03.448
THROUGH THE COIL
AND HE'S TYING THE SHOT,

07:03.448 --> 07:06.103
HE COULD BE THE GUY THAT GOES
"SHWOOP OOP" RIGHT OVER.

07:06.103 --> 07:08.206
THAT COULD HAVE BEEN
THE END OF D.J. RIGHT THERE,

07:08.206 --> 07:10.551
NEVER SEEN HIS BABY BE BORN.

07:10.551 --> 07:13.172
IT HAPPENS THAT FAST
OUT HERE.

07:14.586 --> 07:16.344
Narrator:
STUCK IN 25-FOOT SEAS

07:16.344 --> 07:18.310
WITH NO WAY
TO HAUL THEIR POTS...

07:20.103 --> 07:21.896
THIS IS NOT WHAT WE NEEDED.

07:21.896 --> 07:23.758
...THE BROKEN PICKING HOOK

07:23.758 --> 07:26.724
SLAMS THE BREAKS ON CASEY
AND JOSH'S HOT STREAK.

07:26.724 --> 07:28.724
Casey: I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S
GOING ON WITH THE CRANE HERE.

07:28.724 --> 07:30.275
YOU'VE GOT TO DIAGNOSE IT,
FIGURE IT OUT,

07:30.275 --> 07:31.655
AND GO FROM THERE.

07:31.655 --> 07:35.241
THIS MIGHT JUST
ABSOLUTELY SCREW US.

07:35.241 --> 07:40.689
♪♪

07:40.689 --> 07:46.172
♪♪

07:48.517 --> 07:50.482
Narrator: 65 MILES WEST...

07:52.586 --> 07:55.068
WATCH RIGHT OF THE BOAT!

07:55.068 --> 07:57.448
CARRY ON.

07:57.448 --> 07:59.586
AAH! WHOA.

07:59.586 --> 08:02.482
OH [BLEEP],
THAT'S A [BLEEP] WAVE.

08:05.862 --> 08:08.000
IT'S A MONSTER.

08:08.000 --> 08:10.655
WOW.

08:10.655 --> 08:12.137
JUST MISSED THAT ONE, MAN.

08:12.137 --> 08:16.241
THAT CAME ROLLING DOWN
THE PORTSIDE BIG-TIME.

08:16.241 --> 08:19.275
Narrator: UNDETERRED BY
THE THREAT OF MASSIVE WAVES,

08:19.275 --> 08:21.655
CAPTAIN KEITH COLBURN
STEERS THE WIZARD

08:21.655 --> 08:25.793
INTO ARCTIC STORM ELSA'S
FROZEN HEART.

08:25.793 --> 08:27.379
TALK ABOUT YEAH! WHOO!

08:27.379 --> 08:31.137
-YEAH, WHOO!
-POW, POW! WHOOP, WHOOP!

08:31.137 --> 08:32.793
Keith: RIGHT NOW,
I THINK WE'RE ABOUT

08:32.793 --> 08:35.172
IN THE MEAT OF THIS STORM, ELSA.

08:35.172 --> 08:36.724
THE PROBLEM IS
IT'S A HUGE STORM,

08:36.724 --> 08:38.413
AND WE'RE GONNA GET THIS
FOR PROBABLY

08:38.413 --> 08:40.482
ANOTHER 24 TO 36 HOURS

08:40.482 --> 08:44.965
OF SUSTAINED EAST NORTHEAST
HEAVY FREEZING SPRAY.

08:44.965 --> 08:46.827
COLD, COLD, COLD.

08:48.068 --> 08:49.482
[ CLANG ]

08:51.931 --> 08:53.517
YOU GUYS ARE GOING GREAT
ON THE DECK.

08:53.517 --> 08:56.793
YOU GUYS KEEP GOING ON THE DECK
TO GET TO BARE WOOD.

08:56.793 --> 08:59.275
YEAH, IT'S FLAT NASTY OUT HERE.

08:59.275 --> 09:02.517
IT'S BEEN A FEW YEARS SINCE I'VE
SEEN ICE LIKE THIS ON THE BOAT.

09:05.206 --> 09:07.551
Roger: YOU KNOW, WE GOT TO TRY
TO KEEP A --

09:07.551 --> 09:11.896
KEEP A HANDLE ON THIS ICE BEFORE
IT GETS OUT OF CONTROL ON US.

09:11.896 --> 09:13.655
NOT JUST THE CRABBING OUT HERE
IS DANGEROUS,

09:13.655 --> 09:16.103
THE WEATHER'S
PRETTY DANGEROUS, TOO.

09:16.103 --> 09:17.896
WATCH OUT.
WAVE COMING STARBOARD SIDE.

09:17.896 --> 09:19.862
HANG ON, HANG ON!

09:19.862 --> 09:21.034
LOOK OUT!

09:22.655 --> 09:24.793
Man: WHEW!

09:24.793 --> 09:27.137
YEAH, LET'S GO AHEAD
AND GET THE GUYS OFF OF THERE.

09:27.137 --> 09:29.103
AS LONG AS IT'S RUNNING,
WE'LL FINISH CHIPPING OUT

09:29.103 --> 09:32.793
BEFORE THE NEXT STRING,
ALL RIGHT?

09:32.793 --> 09:34.551
COMING UP.

09:37.793 --> 09:39.172
21st OF JANUARY,

09:39.172 --> 09:42.517
AND I GOT ABOUT 10,000 POUNDS
OF CRAB ON THIS BOAT.

09:42.517 --> 09:45.862
I MEAN, FOR ME, THIS IS MY FIRST
REAL POT OF THE SEASON.

09:45.862 --> 09:52.379
♪♪

09:52.379 --> 09:56.206
Narrator: AFTER STRIKING OUT
IN THE SOUTH,

09:56.206 --> 10:00.137
KEITH MADE THE 240-MILE TREK
TO THE FAR NORTHWESTERN EDGE

10:00.137 --> 10:01.793
OF THE FISHING GROUNDS.

10:01.793 --> 10:06.344
WE'RE UP NEAR THE 60 LINE RIGHT
NOW, WHICH IS REALLY FAR NORTH,

10:06.344 --> 10:07.931
RIGHT WHERE WE'VE HAD
REALLY HOT FISHING

10:07.931 --> 10:10.862
BEFORE DEEP
IN PERVENETS CANYON.

10:10.862 --> 10:14.517
NOW, HE'S COUNTING ON
THESE DEEP, REMOTE WATERS

10:14.517 --> 10:16.724
TO JUMP-START HIS SEASON.

10:16.724 --> 10:19.896
IT'S FEAST OR FAMINE HERE.

10:19.896 --> 10:23.344
SO, WE JUST GOT TO PLAY UNTIL WE
COME UP WITH SOMETHING UP HERE.

10:23.344 --> 10:25.413
PULL THE FLOATY.
COME ON, BABY.

10:25.413 --> 10:27.206
IT'S A GAMBLE COMING WAY UP
THE HILL FOR THIS.

10:27.206 --> 10:30.344
AND IT'S A LOT OF WORK,
IT'S A LOT OF TIME,

10:30.344 --> 10:33.931
A LOT OF ENERGY JUST TO GET UP
WAY UP NORTH WHERE WE'RE AT NOW.

10:35.965 --> 10:37.551
MAYBE WE'LL GET LUCKY.

10:38.586 --> 10:39.931
BIG BOY, BIG BOY.

10:39.931 --> 10:42.172
OH, BOO.

10:46.931 --> 10:48.517
OH, COME ON.

10:53.551 --> 10:55.482
AY.

10:55.482 --> 10:57.172
DOGGONE IT.

10:57.172 --> 11:00.034
YOU GOTTA BE KIDDING ME!

11:00.034 --> 11:02.241
YEAH, WELL, THAT FIRST POT'S
NOT WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR,

11:02.241 --> 11:03.862
I'LL TELL YOU
THAT RIGHT NOW.

11:06.172 --> 11:07.689
WOW. THERE'S ANOTHER BIG ONE.

11:07.689 --> 11:09.517
[ ALARM BLARES ]

11:11.000 --> 11:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

11:22.931 --> 11:24.724
[BLEEP] WHERE DID THAT THING
COME FROM?

11:30.827 --> 11:33.724
WE'RE ALSO NOT HAULING [BLEEP]
FOR CRABS.

11:33.724 --> 11:35.827
AW, MAN.

11:35.827 --> 11:38.586
NOW, THIS IS
A PRETTY LOSE-LOSE SCENARIO.

11:42.965 --> 11:44.241
Tyler: Who knows?

11:44.241 --> 11:46.517
THAT'S WHY THEY DON'T PAY ME
THE BIG BUCKS.

11:46.517 --> 11:50.448
I STAND OUT ON DECK
AND FREEZE MY ASS OFF.

11:50.448 --> 11:54.931
Keith: MY LITTLE HONEY HOLE IN
THE CANYON WAS A COMPLETE DUD.

11:54.931 --> 11:58.689
LET'S GET THIS GEAR ON
AND GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE,

11:58.689 --> 12:02.724
MOVE TO AN AREA WHERE
HOPEFULLY WE CAN GET WORKING.

12:02.724 --> 12:06.034
Narrator: NO CRAB
OR SIGN OF LIFE IN HIS POTS,

12:06.034 --> 12:08.344
THE CAPTAIN
IS BACK ON THE HUNT...

12:08.344 --> 12:10.620
OH, BACKDOOR NOW. BACKDOOR!

12:10.620 --> 12:11.862
WHOA!

12:11.862 --> 12:13.379
Narrator:
...UNDER CONSTANT THREAT

12:13.379 --> 12:16.586
FROM ELSA'S BUILDING SEAS.

12:16.586 --> 12:18.275
ONE MORE RIGHT BEHIND IT.

12:18.275 --> 12:20.793
[ MEN SHOUTING ]

12:23.586 --> 12:25.172
WELL, I THINK THE TIDE'S
TURNING A LITTLE BIT,

12:25.172 --> 12:29.344
SO IT'S PROBABLY GONNA
GET WORSE, IF THAT'S POSSIBLE.

12:29.344 --> 12:31.379
SO JUST BE PREPARED.

12:31.379 --> 12:34.620
YOU HEAR ME START YELLING, MAN,
START RUNNING AND HANGING ON.

12:37.655 --> 12:40.965
WHOA, WHOA.

12:40.965 --> 12:43.137
HERE WE GO.

12:43.137 --> 12:45.448
OKAY, GUYS, THIS ONE'S
COMING FOR REAL I THINK.

12:45.448 --> 12:47.448
WATCH OUT. HANG ON! HANG ON!

12:47.448 --> 12:49.517
Man: LOOK OUT!

12:49.517 --> 12:51.310
WHOA!

12:53.172 --> 12:55.275
Narrator: ON THE WIZARD...

12:55.275 --> 12:57.344
Keith: HERE WE GO.

12:57.344 --> 12:59.482
OKAY, GUYS, THIS ONE'S
COMING FOR REAL, I THINK.

12:59.482 --> 13:01.448
WATCH OUT. HANG ON! HANG ON!

13:01.448 --> 13:02.965
Man: LOOK OUT!

13:05.206 --> 13:07.241
[ MAN GROANS ]

13:07.241 --> 13:14.034
WHERE AM I GONNA GO?

13:14.034 --> 13:16.413
OH.
EVERYBODY GOOD?

13:16.413 --> 13:19.103
NOT CHASE.

13:23.517 --> 13:26.413
YEAH, YOU GOT TO HOLD
ONTO [BLEEP] DUDE.

13:26.413 --> 13:29.758
[BLEEP]
WILD WEST OUT HERE.

13:29.758 --> 13:31.793
THAT WAS ONE HELL OF A BIG WAVE.

13:31.793 --> 13:34.379
IT CAME IN AND BLINDSIDED US.

13:34.379 --> 13:37.172
WHOA.

13:37.172 --> 13:39.344
Narrator: WHILE THE 5-MAN CREW
HAULS A POT...

13:39.344 --> 13:42.586
HEAD'S UP!
WHERE AM I GONNA GO?

13:42.586 --> 13:49.034
A 40-FOOT, 16,000 GALLON WALL
OF WATER SMASHES WIZARD HEAD ON.

13:49.034 --> 13:52.517
AW.

13:52.517 --> 13:54.551
THAT WOULD HAVE CLEARED THE DECK
AND EVERYBODY ON IT

13:54.551 --> 13:57.068
IF I HIT US
ON THE STARBOARD SIDE.

13:57.068 --> 13:59.931
YEAH, THAT WAS A BRUISER, MAN.

13:59.931 --> 14:02.379
YOU'RE REALLY NEVER IN SHAPE
TO EVER BE OUT HERE

14:02.379 --> 14:04.103
HAULING CRAB POTS,

14:04.103 --> 14:05.482
ESPECIALLY WITH
THE WEATHER LIKE THIS.

14:05.482 --> 14:08.551
IT DOES MAKE IT KIND OF FUN,
THOUGH.

14:08.551 --> 14:12.413
YOU GOT TO BE ON YOUR TOES.
ALL RIGHT.

14:12.413 --> 14:14.965
YOU GOT 38 POTS LEFT
TO PUT ON HERE.

14:18.068 --> 14:19.689
JUST GOT TO GET THIS GEAR
ON THE BOAT,

14:19.689 --> 14:21.137
THAT'S ALL WE GOT
TO DO RIGHT NOW.

14:21.137 --> 14:25.103
JUST GET THE GEAR ON,
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

14:25.103 --> 14:27.275
AND I THINK OUR ONLY OPTION'S
GO EAST.

14:29.379 --> 14:32.551
GET OUT TO THE EAST AND FIND
SOME CRAB IN THE SHALLOWS.

14:32.551 --> 14:40.551
♪♪

14:40.551 --> 14:43.310
Narrator: 80 MILES EAST,

14:43.310 --> 14:44.655
ON THE RUSSIAN LINE...

14:48.137 --> 14:53.137
WHOO-HOO-HOO.

14:53.137 --> 14:56.965
...THE CREW OF THE MAMMOTH
140-FOOT SOUTHERN WIND

14:56.965 --> 15:00.862
TAKE THEIR PUNISHMENT
FROM ELSA'S HATEFUL EMBRACE.

15:05.344 --> 15:06.827
OKAY, WATCH OUT!

15:06.827 --> 15:10.517
♪♪

15:10.517 --> 15:11.965
WHOA!

15:14.379 --> 15:17.344
THERE WE GO! WE'RE GOOD.

15:17.344 --> 15:18.724
IF ONE OF THOSE WAVES,
THE FORCE OF THAT WATER,

15:18.724 --> 15:20.413
IT'LL JUST TAKE YOU
WHEREVER YOU WANT IT.

15:20.413 --> 15:23.586
I MEAN, I'VE HAD GUYS DOING IT
BEFORE, BREAK YOUR COLLARBONE,

15:23.586 --> 15:25.655
SMASH YOUR TEETH.

15:25.655 --> 15:27.206
Narrator:
CAPTAIN STEVE "HARLEY" DAVIDSON

15:27.206 --> 15:29.482
APPROACHES HIS NEXT STRING,

15:29.482 --> 15:32.275
WITH ONE EYE
ON HIS OPILIO POTS

15:32.275 --> 15:36.172
AND THE OTHER HOPING TO SPOT
60-FOOT ROGUE WAVES

15:36.172 --> 15:38.068
BEFORE THEY SPOT HIM.

15:39.275 --> 15:43.103
-AAH! [ LAUGHS ]
-DOUBLE-SHOT!

15:45.172 --> 15:47.000
OKAY, COMING UP.

15:47.000 --> 15:49.724
YEAH!

15:49.724 --> 15:53.655
Narrator: 62,000 INTO HIS
250,000-POUND QUOTA.

15:53.655 --> 15:56.586
COME ON NOW, COME ON NOW.

15:56.586 --> 15:58.758
Narrator: HARLEY LOOKS FOR
HIS NORTHERN HONEY HOLE

15:58.758 --> 16:02.620
TO KEEP PAYING BIG

16:02.620 --> 16:05.413
AND MAKE THEIR BEATINGS
WORTH THE PAIN.

16:09.724 --> 16:13.896
MASSIVE ROLLERS GOING
THAN A HOUSE, YOU KNOW.

16:13.896 --> 16:16.034
KEEPS YOU ON YOUR TOES
FOR SURE.

16:16.034 --> 16:22.413
♪♪

16:22.413 --> 16:24.000
HERE WE ARE.

16:24.000 --> 16:25.620
YOU GOT TO WANT IT.

16:28.241 --> 16:30.000
OH!

16:30.000 --> 16:32.896
-WHOO!
-WHOO!

16:32.896 --> 16:34.275
GONNA BE A LARGE POT.

16:34.275 --> 16:43.586
♪♪

16:43.586 --> 16:46.275
WHAT'S THE NUMBER
ON THAT ONE?

16:46.275 --> 16:50.758
OOH, IT'S TOP-SECRET
INFORMATION.

16:50.758 --> 16:53.517
Munsey: SEE THERE'S QUITE A BIT
OF SORTING GOING ON.

16:53.517 --> 16:56.793
I DON'T THINK IT WAS AS CLEAN
AS THEY THOUGHT IT WAS GONNA BE.

16:56.793 --> 17:00.482
-150.
-150?

17:00.482 --> 17:03.862
OH, BEFORE, THESE WERE LIKE 500.

17:09.068 --> 17:11.103
THAT'S TELLING YOU THE BOTTOM

17:11.103 --> 17:14.550
IS NOT AS PLENTIFUL
AS YOU WERE HOPING.

17:18.827 --> 17:21.378
-NO!
-SO WEAK.

17:21.378 --> 17:26.378
OH, NO. 60. SIX-ZERO.

17:26.378 --> 17:30.034
60 ON THAT ONE? RIGHT?

17:30.034 --> 17:33.000
THESE ARE JUST A LITTLE
TOO SMALL.

17:33.000 --> 17:34.827
WITH MOST OF THE OPILIO
IN HIS POTS

17:34.827 --> 17:38.034
COMING UP SMALLER
THAN THE 3-INCH MINIMUM.

17:38.034 --> 17:42.379
YESTERDAY, MY CLEANEST AND
NICEST CRAB WAS RIGHT AT 72,000.

17:42.379 --> 17:46.586
SAND I THINK I GOT
TO GET BACK OVER THERE.

17:46.586 --> 17:50.344
Narrator: THE CAPTAIN PLOTS
A COURSE CORRECTION.

17:50.344 --> 17:55.551
I SEE THIS LITTLE TOPOGRAPHICAL
MOUND ON MY CHART HERE.

17:55.551 --> 17:58.000
IT'S RIGHT HERE
TO THE SOUTHWEST OF ME.

17:58.000 --> 17:59.896
THIS MOUNTAIN LOOKS LIKE
A LITTLE HOT DOG.

17:59.896 --> 18:02.655
IF IT COMES UP TO 72,000,

18:02.655 --> 18:05.517
I THINK THAT WE GOT
TO GET ON THAT.

18:05.517 --> 18:09.551
HARLEY WILL SHUFFLE HIS GEAR
ONTO AN ELEVATED PLATEAU

18:09.551 --> 18:12.551
KNOWN AS THE HOT DOG,
COUNTING ON THE SHALLOWER DEPTHS

18:12.551 --> 18:15.827
TO PUT HIM BACK
ON THE MEAT.

18:15.827 --> 18:20.068
HERE WE'RE GONNA PUT THIS ONE ON
AND GO OVER TO THE HOT DOG.

18:20.068 --> 18:22.379
HOT DIGGITY DOG!

18:22.379 --> 18:27.103
♪♪

18:27.103 --> 18:29.482
ONCE YOU FIND THEM,
YOU GOT TO KEEP ON THEM.

18:29.482 --> 18:34.206
YOU CAN'T LOSE THEM, IT'S NOT
WHAT A GOOD FISHERMAN DOES.

18:34.206 --> 18:36.620
PEOPLE COULD BE LUCKY
AND STUMBLE ACROSS THEM,

18:36.620 --> 18:38.758
BUT YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO BE
GOOD TO STAY ON THEM.

18:38.758 --> 18:44.689
♪♪

18:44.689 --> 18:46.068
Narrator: COMING UP...

18:46.068 --> 18:49.379
WITH ICE AND EVERYTHING ELSE
THIS IS VERY DANGEROUS.

18:49.379 --> 18:51.206
HOLD ON.
DUDE, BIG WAVE, BIG WAVE!

18:51.206 --> 18:53.310
LOOK OUT!

18:53.310 --> 18:56.517
EVEN THOUGH THE WEATHER'S
HORRIBLE, WE'RE FINDING A WAY.

18:56.517 --> 18:57.965
HANG ON, GUYS, HANG ON,
HANG ON!

18:57.965 --> 19:00.275
HANG ON, HANG ON! AAH!

19:02.758 --> 19:04.413
Narrator:
ON THE FAR NORTHERN WATERS,

19:04.413 --> 19:05.689
JUST SPITTING DISTANCE

19:05.689 --> 19:10.068
FROM PUTIN'S IRON FIST
IS THE CORNELIA MARIE.

19:10.068 --> 19:12.034
IT'S A CRAB BOAT,
CLOSE CALLS HAPPEN A LOT,

19:12.034 --> 19:15.689
THAT ONE I'M THANKFUL
DIDN'T TAKE HIM.

19:15.689 --> 19:17.034
COULD HAVE.

19:17.034 --> 19:20.344
HAVING A PICKING HOOK SNAP
LIKE THAT IS DANGEROUS.

19:20.344 --> 19:22.034
Narrator: A BROKEN CABLE

19:22.034 --> 19:24.103
LEAVES JOSH AND CASEY UNABLE
TO HAUL THEIR POTS.

19:24.103 --> 19:26.413
-Man: WATCH OUT!
-Narrator: BUT THEY'RE LUCKY

19:26.413 --> 19:28.793
THE CONSEQUENCES WEREN'T
MUCH WORSE.

19:28.793 --> 19:30.620
YOU HAUL 10,000 POTS

19:30.620 --> 19:35.586
AND EVERYTHING IS JUST
HUNKY-DORY AND THEN 10,001...

19:35.586 --> 19:37.172
LIGHTS OUT, GAME OVER.

19:40.034 --> 19:42.206
IT'S ALL FUN AND GAMES UNTIL
SOMETHING LIKE THAT HAPPENS.

19:42.206 --> 19:47.068
IT MAKES YOU THINK A LITTLE BIT
ABOUT WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

19:47.068 --> 19:50.448
AFTER REVIEWING THE PLAY,
THE PICKING HOOK WAS JAMMED

19:50.448 --> 19:54.344
ALL THE WAY UP IN THAT BLOCK,
THAT'S WHEN IT SNAPPED.

19:54.344 --> 20:01.517
ONE OF YOU'S GONNA LIFT ME UP TO
THE POT WITH THE PICKING BOOM,

20:01.517 --> 20:04.655
AND WE STILL GOT CABLE
THROUGH THERE

20:04.655 --> 20:08.862
SO WE CAN SPLICE ANOTHER EYE
FOR ANOTHER HOOK.

20:08.862 --> 20:12.068
AS 25-FOOT SEAS HAMMER THE BOAT,

20:12.068 --> 20:15.586
DECKHAND TAYLOR JENSEN
WILL ATTEMPT A HIGH-WIRE ACT

20:15.586 --> 20:17.827
TO THREAD A NEW CABLE
THROUGH THE PULLEY

20:17.827 --> 20:19.448
ATOP THE PICKING BOOM.

20:22.620 --> 20:26.620
MULTIMILLION-DOLLAR OPERATION
HALTED RIGHT NOW

20:26.620 --> 20:29.482
FROM A $200 CABLE.

20:29.482 --> 20:33.862
WITH ICE AND EVERYTHING ELSE,
THIS IS VERY DANGEROUS.

20:33.862 --> 20:38.137
♪♪

20:38.137 --> 20:40.172
ALL RIGHT, LET'S DO IT.
LET'S DO IT.

20:40.172 --> 20:49.413
♪♪

20:49.413 --> 20:58.689
♪♪

20:58.689 --> 21:08.034
♪♪

21:25.655 --> 21:28.827
HOLY [BLEEP], LOOK AT THAT.
THERE IS A RAKER COMING IN.

21:37.931 --> 21:40.034
Man: HOLD ON!

21:41.758 --> 21:43.344
STOP!

21:43.344 --> 21:48.137
♪♪

21:48.137 --> 21:49.586
AAH!

21:51.655 --> 21:54.310
[BLEEP].

21:56.586 --> 21:58.275
[ WHISTLES ]

21:58.275 --> 22:00.034
♪♪

22:00.034 --> 22:02.241
[BLEEP] WATCH OUT, TAYLOR!

22:08.034 --> 22:09.827
DOWN SLOW!

22:09.827 --> 22:17.724
♪♪

22:19.586 --> 22:21.827
TAYLOR IS A BAD-ASS.

22:22.862 --> 22:24.482
[BLEEP], MAN.

22:30.551 --> 22:32.517
THAT WAS SCARY.

22:32.517 --> 22:34.965
THAT WAS SCARY.
I DIDN'T LIKE THAT AT ALL.

22:34.965 --> 22:38.448
WITH THE LINE THREADED,
THE CREW RE-ATTACHES THE HOOK

22:38.448 --> 22:41.000
AND SPOOLS THE SLACK
INTO THE DRUM.

22:41.000 --> 22:42.344
HEY!

22:42.344 --> 22:45.862
THE QUICK FIX
GETS THE CORNELIA MARIE

22:45.862 --> 22:47.413
BACK IN ACTION.

22:47.413 --> 22:51.103
BUT THE FISHING GROUND
STILL FIRMLY IN ELSA'S GRASP,

22:51.103 --> 22:55.793
SWELLS CONTINUE TO BUILD
IN HEIGHT AND FREQUENCY.

22:55.793 --> 22:57.965
THE WEATHER'S
NOT LOOKING PRETTY,

22:57.965 --> 23:00.689
BUT THAT'S NOT GONNA
STOP US FROM FISHING.

23:00.689 --> 23:04.137
WHOO!
IF IT GETS REALLY, REALLY BAD,

23:04.137 --> 23:05.620
WE'LL MAKE THAT CALL
AT THAT TIME,

23:05.620 --> 23:08.827
BUT UNTIL THEN, I'M GONNA PLAN
ON FISH THROUGH ALL OF IT.

23:08.827 --> 23:10.724
YEAH-HA!

23:10.724 --> 23:15.655
♪♪

23:15.655 --> 23:17.827
JUST 15 MILES SOUTH..,

23:20.862 --> 23:23.275
-WATCH OUT. WATCH OUT!
-HOLD ON!

23:23.275 --> 23:26.827
♪♪

23:26.827 --> 23:31.103
THIS IS BERING SEA FISHING, MAN.

23:31.103 --> 23:33.103
THAT'S WHAT YOU GET OUT HERE.

23:36.965 --> 23:40.413
WHERE YOU AT?

23:40.413 --> 23:41.862
YEAH!

23:41.862 --> 23:45.103
Narrator: SOUTHERN WIND SKIPPER
STEVE "HARLEY" DAVIDSON

23:45.103 --> 23:49.793
SETS INTO MOUNTING
UNFORGIVING SEAS.

23:49.793 --> 23:52.551
THERE'S THIS LITTLE MOUND
RIGHT HERE, IT'S AT 72,

23:52.551 --> 23:54.448
AND I THINK
THAT'S WHERE THEY'RE GOING.

23:54.448 --> 23:56.448
Narrator:
COUNTING ON A ROCKY PLATEAU

23:56.448 --> 23:57.793
KNOWN AS THE HOT DOG

23:57.793 --> 23:59.931
TO GET HIS OPILIO SEASON COOKING
AGAIN.

24:03.344 --> 24:05.724
OH!
WATCH OUT!

24:05.724 --> 24:09.034
IF THEY GET UP ON THAT HOT DOG,

24:09.034 --> 24:11.310
I THINK I'M GONNA FIND
SOME BIGGER, CLEAN CRAB.

24:11.310 --> 24:13.206
YEAH.

24:13.206 --> 24:17.689
IF WE FIND THEM LIKE WE DID
THAT FIRST SET THROUGH HERE --

24:17.689 --> 24:22.724
WE DID, YOU KNOW, 400 AVERAGE
WHICH IS REALLY HIGH NUMBER.

24:22.724 --> 24:27.275
IF I WERE TO LOSE THAT LITTLE
BITE OF CRAB THAT I WAS ON,

24:27.275 --> 24:28.793
THAT WOULD BE
THE MOST FRUSTRATING THING

24:28.793 --> 24:33.275
THAT COULD HAPPEN IS TO FIND
THEM AND THEN TO LOSE THEM.

24:36.310 --> 24:40.275
WITH HARLEY LOOKING TO GET
HIS GROOVE BACK,

24:40.275 --> 24:43.586
80 MILES WEST...

24:43.586 --> 24:47.137
OKAY, COMING UP OVER YOUR HEAD!

24:47.137 --> 24:49.103
HEAD'S UP, READY.
NO PLAY, NO PLAY.

24:49.103 --> 24:51.724
HEAD'S UP!

24:51.724 --> 24:54.586
Narrator: KEITH TANGOS
WITH ELSA'S CHURNING SEAS,

24:54.586 --> 24:57.275
STILL LOOKING
FOR THE SPARK HE NEEDS

24:57.275 --> 24:59.793
TO SET HIS OPILIO SEASON
ON FIRE.

24:59.793 --> 25:04.655
♪♪

25:04.655 --> 25:07.965
WE CAME UP WITH NOTHING
IN OUR OLD HOT SPOT,

25:07.965 --> 25:11.103
AND WE NEED SOMETHING
TO SHOW UP HERE.

25:11.103 --> 25:13.103
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO!

25:13.103 --> 25:15.241
Keith: I WAS NERVOUS ABOUT
MAKING THIS MOVE WITH THIS GEAR,

25:15.241 --> 25:17.793
BUT I DON'T
HAVE ANY OPTIONS.

25:17.793 --> 25:21.344
NO CRAB OUT WEST,
I CAN GUARANTEE YOU THAT.

25:21.344 --> 25:22.586
GETTING UP SHALLOW.

25:22.586 --> 25:26.000
WE GOT ABOUT 130 POTS ON HERE,

25:26.000 --> 25:29.620
AND WE'VE GOT 70 POTS
LEFT DOWN IN THE CANYON.

25:29.620 --> 25:32.689
THERE'S NO WAY I CAN A 200-POT
STACK ON THIS BOAT RIGHT NOW,

25:32.689 --> 25:35.620
SO WE'RE LEAN AND MEAN.

25:37.620 --> 25:38.862
Narrator: THE 30-FOOT SEAS

25:38.862 --> 25:40.827
THREATENING THE STABILITY
OF HIS VESSEL,

25:40.827 --> 25:45.655
KEITH MUST STACK AND MOVE
ALL 200 POTS IN TWO TRIPS,

25:45.655 --> 25:49.172
MITIGATING HIS RISK
AS HE CONTINUES TO PERSEVERE

25:49.172 --> 25:52.103
ELSA'S TORTUOUS TENURE.

25:52.103 --> 25:55.034
I'M GONNA CLEAR THE ENTIRE DECK,
TURN AROUND,

25:55.034 --> 25:58.103
AND "PEW"
RIGHT BACK TO THE CANYON

25:58.103 --> 26:01.413
AND GET THE REST OF THE GEAR.

26:01.413 --> 26:03.137
Man: GO, GO, GO!

26:03.137 --> 26:05.000
HEY, WHO'S THERE,
YOU CAN GET THAT?

26:05.000 --> 26:11.068
ROGER!
OKAY, GO AND LET IT GO.

26:11.068 --> 26:14.275
ALL GOOD.

26:14.275 --> 26:19.896
EVEN THOUGH THE WEATHER'S
HORRIBLE, WE'RE FINDING A WAY.

26:19.896 --> 26:22.379
SENT A BUNCH STRANGE AND CHARGE

26:22.379 --> 26:24.793
BACK TO GET
THE REST OF THE GEAR.

26:24.793 --> 26:26.241
LET'S START OUR SEASON.

26:26.241 --> 26:28.068
I THINK WE'VE HAD ENOUGH
PRACTICE.

26:30.655 --> 26:32.310
TIME TO GO CATCH SOME CRAB.

26:35.931 --> 26:38.586
520 MILES NORTH OF
DUTCH HARBOR...

26:42.620 --> 26:44.724
WHOA!

26:44.724 --> 26:48.137
...ELSA'S UNRELENTING
SINGLE-DIGIT TEMPERATURES

26:48.137 --> 26:51.517
AND THUNDERING WAVES
ROCK THE CORNELIA MARIE.

26:58.827 --> 27:02.068
THIS IS SOME SERIOUSLY [BLEEP]
WEATHER TO BE HAULING GEAR IN.

27:02.068 --> 27:04.275
WITH THEIR PICKING HOOK
RETHREADED,

27:06.517 --> 27:09.862
CASEY AND JOSH
ARE BACK TO HAULING POTS.

27:09.862 --> 27:12.448
WE'RE STILL DOING STRONG
FISHING-WISE.

27:12.448 --> 27:14.620
POTS ARE COMING UP FULL.

27:14.620 --> 27:17.172
WE JUST HAVE SPRAY COMING ON
RIGHT NOW, AND SPRAY SUCKS.

27:17.172 --> 27:19.172
AND WE HAVE BIG ROLLS,
AND WITH FULL POTS,

27:19.172 --> 27:21.862
BIG ROLLS SUCK.
WHOA.

27:21.862 --> 27:26.517
[BLEEP] WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WATCH OUT.

27:26.517 --> 27:28.931
GET IT?

27:28.931 --> 27:32.413
HOLY [BLEEP].

27:32.413 --> 27:33.793
LOOK AT THAT ONE.

27:33.793 --> 27:35.413
THAT ONE'S TALLER
THAN THE MAST.

27:35.413 --> 27:40.344
♪♪

27:40.344 --> 27:42.172
AAH!

27:45.862 --> 27:47.551
IF WE GET THESE SHUFFLED,

27:47.551 --> 27:50.724
IT'S FISHABLE, SAFELY FISHABLE.

27:50.724 --> 27:53.620
[ MEN SHOUT INDISTINCTLY ]

27:53.620 --> 27:55.448
LOOK OUT!

27:59.275 --> 28:01.862
WE'RE NOT GONNA
PUSH OUR LUCK ANY FARTHER...

28:02.965 --> 28:05.724
-ROGER!
-ALL RIGHT!

28:05.724 --> 28:07.965
Man:
DO YOU WANT THEM IN SQUARE?

28:07.965 --> 28:13.379
Narrator: CASEY'S PLAN --
CHANGE COURSE AND RESET HIS GEAR

28:13.379 --> 28:17.034
TO PROTECT HIS FREEZING MEN
FROM THE WIND AND WAVES.

28:22.689 --> 28:24.275
Man:
GIVE IT A LITTLE TENSION.

28:26.724 --> 28:28.103
[ METAL CREAKS ]

28:33.413 --> 28:35.206
[ METAL CREAKS ]

28:35.206 --> 28:38.310
HEY! HOLD ON! HOLD ON!
HOLD ON! HOLD ON!

28:38.310 --> 28:43.000
♪♪

28:43.000 --> 28:44.758
[BLEEP]! DAMN IT!

28:44.758 --> 28:48.379
Narrator: JUST HOURS AFTER
THEIR PICKING LINE SNAPPED...

28:50.275 --> 28:52.103
IT WON'T COME DOWN!

28:52.103 --> 28:55.689
...THE PORTSIDE CRANE SEIZES UP.

28:55.689 --> 28:57.931
Casey:
THIS IS NOT WHAT WE NEEDED.

29:01.827 --> 29:03.344
WHY?

29:09.034 --> 29:10.241
[BLEEP].

29:11.379 --> 29:13.172
[ CLANK ]

29:13.172 --> 29:16.068
BACK IN THE HARNESS.

29:16.068 --> 29:18.827
IF THAT AIN'T DEDICATION,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IS.

29:18.827 --> 29:22.827
I CAN'T MISS ANY BREAKS
TODAY.

29:24.379 --> 29:28.068
Narrator: FOR THE SECOND TIME,
DECKHAND TAYLOR JENSEN

29:28.068 --> 29:32.517
MAKES A PRECARIOUS ASCENT
2 STORIES ABOVE THE ICY DECK.

29:32.517 --> 29:40.172
♪♪

29:42.482 --> 29:45.103
Man: IT'S BROKEN OFF?

29:45.103 --> 29:46.517
OH, [BLEEP].

29:46.517 --> 29:49.448
WE'RE GONNA DIE
IN THIS [BLEEP].

29:49.448 --> 29:53.689
HE SAYS ONE OF THE BOLTS IS
BROKEN IN THE TOP HAT.

29:53.689 --> 29:57.724
LIKE, THE TOP OF
THAT BOLT HEAD IS MISSING.

29:57.724 --> 30:01.068
IF THAT'S THE CASE,
THAT COULD CAUSE THAT THING

30:01.068 --> 30:02.965
TO DROP INSIDE OF THERE.

30:02.965 --> 30:05.620
Narrator:
THE BOLTS ON THE ROTO SEAL
HAVE SNAPPED CLEAN OFF,

30:05.620 --> 30:08.586
PREVENTING THE ARM
FROM ROTATING.

30:08.586 --> 30:12.896
IN OTHER WORDS, THE HYDRAULIC
CRANE ARM AIN'T MOVING.

30:14.068 --> 30:15.793
Josh:
SO HOW DO WE FIX THAT?

30:15.793 --> 30:18.137
YOU HAVE TO TAKE THE WHOLE
[BLEEP] THING APART.

30:18.137 --> 30:19.620
SOMETHING WE DO
OUT HERE?

30:21.241 --> 30:23.965
YES AND NO.

30:23.965 --> 30:25.482
OHH.

30:28.000 --> 30:30.655
I NEED TO GO LOOK AT THIS.

30:30.655 --> 30:32.137
Narrator:
THE TIME AND MONEY LOST

30:32.137 --> 30:35.482
IN A 3-DAY STEAM BACK TO PORT

30:35.482 --> 30:38.068
WOULD TURN CASEY AND JOSH'S
FAR NORTH GAMBLE

30:38.068 --> 30:40.793
INTO A LOSING GAME
OF RUSSIAN ROULETTE.

30:43.379 --> 30:47.206
Josh: CASEY'S ONE OF THE BEST
MECHANICS ON THE PLANET,

30:47.206 --> 30:49.655
SO...

30:49.655 --> 30:51.827
HOPEFULLY WE CAN GET
THIS DONE AS FAST AS POSSIBLE.

30:51.827 --> 30:58.000
♪♪

30:58.000 --> 31:01.862
THIS IS, LIKE,
DUTCH HARBOR CALLED

31:01.862 --> 31:04.965
THE HYDRAULIC SPECIALIST GUY
TO WORK HERE.

31:04.965 --> 31:07.551
RIGHT NOW, WE'RE 480 MILES
AWAY FROM DUTCH,

31:07.551 --> 31:10.758
SO WE'RE GONNA TRY
TO FIX THIS ON OUR OWN.

31:10.758 --> 31:17.655
♪♪

31:17.655 --> 31:21.206
Narrator: 10 MILES SOUTH...

31:21.206 --> 31:24.068
Harley: OH, YEAH!

31:24.068 --> 31:26.482
...THE SOUTHERN WINDFIGHTS
30-FOOT SEAS

31:26.482 --> 31:29.275
TO THE TOP OF THEIR STRING.

31:29.275 --> 31:34.275
GRAY, WINDY, BIG WAVES...

31:34.275 --> 31:36.310
THIS IS BERING SEA FISHING, MAN.

31:38.448 --> 31:40.793
Narrator: AFTER FOLLOWING
SIGNS OF LIFE

31:40.793 --> 31:45.000
TO A 72-FATHOM ROCKY PLATEAU
KNOWN AS THE HOT DOG...

31:45.000 --> 31:47.551
I BELIEVE, YOU KNOW, FROM
THE WAY MY GEAR WAS RUNNING,

31:47.551 --> 31:49.206
AND THE WAY THE CRAB SEEMED
TO BE MOVING,

31:49.206 --> 31:52.344
THAT THERE WAS GONNA BE SOME
NICE, CLEAN CRAB UP IN THERE.

31:52.344 --> 31:55.551
...HARLEY'S COUNTING ON THIS SET
TO REWARD THE PUNISHMENT

31:55.551 --> 31:57.655
HIS CREW HAS TAKEN ON DECK

31:57.655 --> 32:00.724
WITH A TANK-STUFFING RUN
OF LOADED POTS.

32:00.724 --> 32:10.689
♪♪

32:10.689 --> 32:11.827
OKAY, HERE IT COMES.

32:11.827 --> 32:13.862
FIRST POT COMING UP, GUYS.

32:13.862 --> 32:15.620
SEE HOW IT GOES.

32:20.241 --> 32:22.068
Danny: PULLING THE FIRST POT!

32:22.068 --> 32:24.655
WE JUST RAN SOME GEAR DOWN
TO THE HOT DOG...

32:28.034 --> 32:32.413
...HOPING THAT WE GET --
IT LOOKS GOOD.

32:32.413 --> 32:34.448
WE'LL SEE HOW IT WORKS OUT.

32:38.448 --> 32:40.103
THIS ISN'T
THAT LONG A SOAK, EITHER.

32:40.103 --> 32:43.206
I THINK...WHAT DO WE GOT?
LIKE, 17 HOURS?

32:49.275 --> 32:50.448
HERE IT COMES, BABY!

32:50.448 --> 32:52.068
HOT POT!

32:56.827 --> 32:58.172
Narrator: THIS WEEK,

32:58.172 --> 33:00.413
"SALTY TAKES"
GOES BEHIND THE SCENES.

33:01.655 --> 33:02.827
WELL, THE CAMERA GUY'S

33:02.827 --> 33:04.172
KIND OF PUTTING HIMSELF
AT RISK RIGHT NOW.

33:04.172 --> 33:06.310
HE'S TRYING TO CLEAN
THE DECK CAMERA.

33:08.551 --> 33:10.586
Narrator:
A STORM ENDANGERS LIVES...

33:10.586 --> 33:13.068
WE HAVEN'T HAD MUCH OF A SHOT
ON THAT CAMERA FOR A WHILE

33:13.068 --> 33:15.034
BECAUSE IT'S BEEN COVERED
IN ICE.

33:15.034 --> 33:16.931
...AND CAMERA LENSES.

33:19.586 --> 33:22.655
♪♪

33:22.655 --> 33:24.034
Narrator:
WHEN MOTHER NATURE'S MAD,

33:24.034 --> 33:26.034
SHE GIVES NO RELIEF
TO FISHERMEN...

33:29.965 --> 33:31.275
-NO WAY!
-Producer: YEAH.

33:31.275 --> 33:32.517
WHAT HAPPENED?

33:32.517 --> 33:34.344
...OR CAMERA CREW.

33:36.551 --> 33:38.586
Narrator: GOTTA LOVE
AN EQUAL OPPORTUNIST.

33:38.586 --> 33:41.620
[ LAUGHING ]

33:41.620 --> 33:43.034
Narrator: THANKS, ELSA.

33:43.034 --> 33:44.379
Keith: WE GET
A LITTLE WINDSHIELD WIPER

33:44.379 --> 33:45.827
ON THAT OR SOMETHING.

33:45.827 --> 33:48.862
♪♪

33:48.862 --> 33:52.000
Narrator: WELL, LOOK WHO'S MADE
THEIR WAY TO THE POLL POSITION.

33:52.000 --> 33:54.586
NOW LET'S SEE IF THEY CAN HOLD
ON TO THEIR ADVANTAGE.

33:57.103 --> 34:00.275
[ BIRDS CALLING ]

34:00.275 --> 34:02.206
Narrator:
ON THE SOUTHERN WIND...

34:02.206 --> 34:03.793
THIS ISN'T THAT LONG A SOAK,
EITHER.

34:03.793 --> 34:06.620
I THINK...WHAT DO WE GOT?
LIKE, 17 HOURS?

34:09.413 --> 34:12.827
...AFTER CHASING THE CRAB TO
A 72-FATHOM UNDERWATER PLATEAU

34:12.827 --> 34:15.206
CALLED THE HOT DOG,

34:15.206 --> 34:17.862
CAPTAIN "HARLEY" DAVIDSON
AND HIS STORM-DRENCHED CREW

34:17.862 --> 34:20.965
LOOK FOR ANY SIGN THAT
THEY ARE BACK ON THE BIOMASS.

34:23.585 --> 34:26.413
Man: HERE IT COMES, BABY!
HOT POT!

34:26.413 --> 34:34.620
♪♪

34:34.620 --> 34:36.655
WHOO!

34:36.655 --> 34:38.827
IT'S A WINNER!

34:38.827 --> 34:40.724
YEAH!

34:40.724 --> 34:42.757
OH, YEAH!

34:42.757 --> 34:45.379
THERE'S A LOT
OF CRAB THERE, MAN.

34:45.379 --> 34:47.965
Narrator: THE VETERAN'S
FIRST SERVING ON THE HOT DOG

34:47.965 --> 34:49.688
COMES UP WITH ALL THE FIXINGS.

34:49.688 --> 34:51.103
YEAH!

34:51.103 --> 34:52.827
HOLY [BLEEP].

34:55.482 --> 34:57.551
THERE'S A COUPLE OF CRAB
IN THERE.

34:57.551 --> 35:00.827
I THINK THAT'S PROBABLY
CLOSE TO A 500.

35:00.827 --> 35:03.482
Harley:
NICE, BIG, CLEAN CRAB.

35:05.862 --> 35:07.689
THESE THINGS ARE PRETTY SOLID.

35:11.827 --> 35:15.068
FOUR...FOUR...ZERO.

35:15.068 --> 35:16.379
4-4-0.

35:16.379 --> 35:18.586
OKAY. OKAY.

35:18.586 --> 35:22.206
THAT'S STILL PRETTY GOOD.
I'LL TAKE THAT EVERY DAY.

35:23.931 --> 35:26.413
SECOND ONE COMING UP.

35:26.413 --> 35:28.068
OH, YEAH!

35:28.068 --> 35:29.551
OH, WOW!

35:31.896 --> 35:34.758
JEEZ, MAN! [ CHUCKLES ]
THAT'S A GOOD ONE.

35:36.448 --> 35:39.620
THAT WAS A HUGE POT RIGHT THERE.

35:39.620 --> 35:42.620
BIG TABLE FULL OF CRABS.

35:42.620 --> 35:45.482
Man: WHOO-HOO!

35:45.482 --> 35:47.413
FOUR-SEVEN-ZERO.

35:47.413 --> 35:49.275
RIGHT! GOOD DEAL!

35:50.517 --> 35:52.862
Man: AW!

35:52.862 --> 35:56.862
Narrator: AFTER DAYS OF FREEZING
WINDS AND CRUSHING WAVES...

35:56.862 --> 35:59.896
-WHOO!
-ANOTHER WINNER, MAN.

35:59.896 --> 36:03.000
...CAPTAIN HARLEY PUTS HIS CREW
BACK ON THE MEAT.

36:03.000 --> 36:06.275
SEE IF WE CAN GET 600
OUT OF THIS ONE.

36:06.275 --> 36:08.758
OKAY. LOOK AT THAT! GOD!

36:08.758 --> 36:10.206
HOLY [BLEEP]!

36:11.551 --> 36:13.689
Munsey: HOT DOG'S
WORKING OUT JUST FINE.

36:17.034 --> 36:19.413
Narrator: 10 MILES NORTH...

36:23.896 --> 36:25.379
...ON THE CORNELIA MARIE...

36:25.379 --> 36:28.344
Man: THERE'S TOO MUCH ICE.
THERE'S NOT ENOUGH ALIGNMENT.

36:28.344 --> 36:29.482
THERE'S NOT ENOUGH LIGHT.

36:29.482 --> 36:31.448
THERE'S NOT ENOUGH
[BLEEP] ANYTHING.

36:31.448 --> 36:35.034
LIKE, I PHYSICALLY
CAN'T [BLEEP] DO IT.

36:40.586 --> 36:43.379
...CRAMPED INSIDE
THE 3-FOOT WIDE BASE,

36:43.379 --> 36:47.896
CO-CAPTAIN CASEY McMANUS RACES
TO FIX THE PORTSIDE CRANE.

36:57.620 --> 37:00.137
Narrator: VIBRATIONS
CAUSED BY A BROKEN BOLT

37:00.137 --> 37:04.724
SHOOK THE CRANE'S ROTATING
MECHANISM LOOSE FROM ITS SEAT.

37:04.724 --> 37:07.482
THE BALANCE FOR A SEASON
HANGS IN THIS FIX.

37:10.517 --> 37:13.448
Narrator: IT'S UP TO CASEY
TO RESECURE THE LOOSE PARTS

37:13.448 --> 37:15.827
TO AVOID FURTHER DAMAGE

37:15.827 --> 37:19.241
AND GET THE CRANE
AND THEIR SEASON BACK ONLINE.

37:19.241 --> 37:20.413
Josh: WELL, MY DAD SAYS

37:20.413 --> 37:22.482
THERE'S THREE TYPES OF PEOPLE
IN THIS WORLD --

37:22.482 --> 37:24.137
PEOPLE THAT
WATCH [BLEEP] HAPPEN,

37:24.137 --> 37:26.137
THERE'S PEOPLE THAT
MAKE [BLEEP] HAPPEN,

37:26.137 --> 37:28.310
AND THERE'S PEOPLE THAT WONDER
WHAT THE [BLEEP] JUST HAPPENED.

37:28.310 --> 37:29.931
DON'T BE NUMBER 3.

37:38.241 --> 37:40.413
[ GROANS, BLEEP ]

37:40.413 --> 37:46.241
♪♪

37:46.241 --> 37:52.103
♪♪

37:52.103 --> 37:54.517
[ WRENCH CLICKING ]

37:54.517 --> 37:56.034
Man: YEAH?

37:56.034 --> 37:58.310
-Casey: ALL RIGHT.
-THERE!

37:58.310 --> 38:04.551
♪♪

38:04.551 --> 38:10.758
♪♪

38:10.758 --> 38:12.655
HOW WE DOING THERE, CAP?

38:18.206 --> 38:20.758
LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE
TESTING IT RIGHT NOW.

38:20.758 --> 38:28.482
♪♪

38:28.482 --> 38:31.448
[ CHEERING ]

38:31.448 --> 38:33.482
Josh: WE GOT IT FIXED.

38:33.482 --> 38:35.344
Man: WHOO!

38:36.862 --> 38:38.206
Casey: IT WAS A NIGHTMARE,

38:38.206 --> 38:40.379
BUT WE SHOULD
BE IN A POSITION NOW

38:40.379 --> 38:42.620
WHERE ALL THE FUNCTIONS
SHOULD WORK AGAIN.

38:44.586 --> 38:46.241
Narrator:
JOSH AND CASEY MAY HAVE PUT

38:46.241 --> 38:48.000
THEIR EQUIPMENT PROBLEMS
BEHIND THEM...

38:48.000 --> 38:51.862
GETTING BY
30, 35-FOOT SEAS OUT HERE,

38:51.862 --> 38:53.758
SUB-ZERO TEMPERATURES.

38:53.758 --> 38:57.862
...BUT THE ICE-COLD FURY OF ELSA
ISN'T GOING ANYWHERE.

38:57.862 --> 38:59.586
CRAB FISHING WASN'T
INTENSE ALREADY,

38:59.586 --> 39:01.000
THEN YOU ADD
THIS [BLEEP] TO IT --

39:01.000 --> 39:03.931
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
IT'S GETTING REAL.

39:06.551 --> 39:10.275
Casey: MARKS THE END
TO A REALLY [BLEEP] DAY.

39:10.275 --> 39:13.827
♪♪

39:13.827 --> 39:15.827
Narrator: 70 MILES WEST...

39:19.206 --> 39:20.655
...ON THE WIZARD...

39:20.655 --> 39:24.448
ONE'S COMING BACK THERE,
BACK SIDE, BACKDOOR, BACKDOOR.

39:30.379 --> 39:32.137
...CAPTAIN KEITH BARRELS THROUGH

39:32.137 --> 39:34.965
WHAT HAVE GROWN TO BE
40-FOOT SEAS,

39:34.965 --> 39:37.379
STACKING ON THE SECOND HALF
OF HIS GEAR

39:37.379 --> 39:40.482
TO COMPLETE HIS MOVE
TO SHALLOWER EASTERN WATERS.

39:40.482 --> 39:42.620
EVERY FEW MINUTES, WE'RE GETTING
A PRETTY GOOD SIZE WAVE

39:42.620 --> 39:46.344
COME ROLLING THROUGH HERE THAT'S
LITERALLY COMING THE WORK ZONE,

39:46.344 --> 39:49.068
OVER THE PORTSIDE,
OVER THE BOW.

39:50.931 --> 39:53.586
Man: OH, NO!

39:53.586 --> 39:55.172
Keith: JUST GOTTA
GET THIS GEAR ON THE BOAT.

39:55.172 --> 39:56.793
THAT'S ALL WE GOTTA DO
RIGHT NOW.

39:56.793 --> 39:59.310
NOT GONNA BE A NICE RIDE
BACK UP THE HILL.

39:59.310 --> 40:02.482
Narrator: BUT THE POWER OF ELSA
TURNS EVERY MILE

40:02.482 --> 40:05.655
INTO A RELENTLESS,
FROZEN GAUNTLET.

40:05.655 --> 40:11.586
♪♪

40:11.586 --> 40:13.551
Keith: RIGHT NOW, I'M JUST
ONE POT AT A TIME.

40:15.793 --> 40:17.620
YO.

40:17.620 --> 40:18.827
HAUL ONE...

40:20.482 --> 40:22.862
...TRY AND KEEP THE GUYS SAFE
AND STACK IT.

40:22.862 --> 40:27.034
♪♪

40:27.034 --> 40:28.241
HAUL ONE...

40:30.551 --> 40:31.862
...KEEP 'EM SAFE,
GET IT STACKED.

40:35.379 --> 40:36.793
I THINK I'M GONNA
GET THROUGH THIS.

40:36.793 --> 40:38.379
YES, I'M GONNA GET THROUGH THIS.

40:38.379 --> 40:46.275
♪♪

40:46.275 --> 40:47.448
WHOA!

40:49.896 --> 40:51.793
THAT WAS GONNA TAKE YOU
THE [BLEEP] OUT.

40:51.793 --> 40:58.034
♪♪

40:58.034 --> 41:01.241
Keith: GOD, THAT WAVE
ON THE PORTSIDE'S A MONSTER.

41:01.241 --> 41:03.034
IT'S GONNA THROW THE BOAT OVER.
DAMN IT.

41:03.034 --> 41:05.896
LOOK AT THAT WAVE
OUT YOUR SIDE, GUYS.

41:07.689 --> 41:09.275
HANG ON, GUYS!
HANG ON! HANG ON!

41:09.275 --> 41:10.862
HANG ON! HANG ON!

41:12.551 --> 41:14.931
Man: AAH! AAH!

41:14.931 --> 41:19.310
♪♪

41:19.310 --> 41:22.206
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

41:22.206 --> 41:24.827
DARN IT. WE GOT ONE GUY DOWN.

41:26.137 --> 41:28.620
GIVE ME A HEAD COUNT.
WE GOT FIVE GUYS, RIGHT?

41:29.689 --> 41:33.379
[ BIRDS CALLING ]

